<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>No whining here</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Ice">Ice</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:29 p.m. 25/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> No whining here<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2091" TARGET=_self>Less XP loss is absolute BS</A> (Benign)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I have never whined to vernant personally about loosing exp, just happy they are helping reduce it, not everyone can play as much as others, and we have friends who can that we have known since the uo days who we couldnt group with because of the huge level differences, this should help us some. Let me guess your character is 18-50ish and can play alot, thats great. But some of us cant, this might help us out. Dieing sucks the way it is anyway; im a warrior, and usually have to run a very long distance to retrieve my body, and along the way its easy to die again.. Figure it this way; say you are level 12 and when you die, it takes you roughly 2 hours or so to get back to your body and get the experience you lost back. Now add to the factor you only get 4 hours of game play tops a day, if you are lucky and you will see what most of us are saying. Its easy if you have time to play not to see the problems some of us face in EQ on the pvp server, trying to catch up.

<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
